title.@value: Gestational oedema or proteinuria without hypertension

definition.@value: A condition affecting pregnant females, characterised by excessive systemic fluid build-up and serum proteins in the urine, without an abnormally elevated blood pressure induced by pregnancy.

label.@value: Pregnancy-induced oedema and proteinuria without hypertension
